The paper deals with predicting user responses in Real-Time Bidding (RTB) using neural embedding techniques. This involves working with sparse categorical features and using distributed representations of features from users' web history to improve the accuracy of prediction models. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves working with real-world data sets, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
